  "why": "The NLC method is designed and evaluated to steer fuzzing toward inputs that diversify layer-wise output distributions and thereby uncover broad classes of security-violating behaviors (e.g., misclassifications, adversarial examples across many target classes). The paper demonstrates that NLC-guided mutation finds many faults and yields high class-coverage/diversity (see fuzzing results and tables). However, the paper does not demonstrate steering toward attacker-chosen, specific target outputs (e.g., forcing a model to output one particular target label or a specific attacker-specified payload). Although the design mentions a class-conditional extension of Σ, the work does not evaluate or show targeted-attack generation in the experiments. Thus NLC supports and demonstrates steering toward broader failure classes but not targeted attack discovery.",
